Preheat your #oven to 200°C. Trim the @aubergine{1} then halve lengthways. Chop each half into 4 long strips then chop widthways into roughly 1cm pieces. Pop the aubergine pieces onto a large #baking tray (use two if necessary) and drizzle with @olive oil{}. Toss to coat then spread out and roast on the top shelf of your oven until soft and golden, ~{20-25%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, bring a #medium saucepan{} of water up to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the pasta. Chop the @black olives{30}(chopped into small pieces). Quarter the @baby plum tomatoes{125}(quartered). Roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{1}(roughly chopped) (stalks and all). Halve, peel and chop the @echalion shallot{1}(peeled and chopped into small pieces). Peel and grate the @garlic clove{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Drain and rinse the @brown lentils{1%180g can} in a #sieve. When the water is boiling, add the @rigatoni pasta{180} and cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}. Once cooked, drain in a #colander and pop back in the pan. Drizzle with @olive oil{1%tbsp} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

While the pasta cooks, heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Add the shallot to the pan and fry until softened, ~{3-4%minutes}. Add in the garlic, @Italian style herbs{1%tsp}, @sun-dried tomato paste{1%tbsp} and the @sugar{1%tsp}. Stir through and cook for ~{1%minute}.

Pour the @finely chopped tomatoes{1%400g can}, @red wine stock paste{1%tbsp}, lentils and @water{50%ml} into the #shallot pan{}. Bring to the boil and stir to combine. Simmer until starting to thicken, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Meanwhile, put the olives, half the plum tomatoes and half the parsley in a #small bowl{} along with the @olive oil{for the salsa}. Season with @pepper{} and stir together.

Add the remaining plum tomatoes and roasted aubergine to the pan. Stir together and simmer for a further ~{3-4%minutes}, then season to taste with @salt and @pepper if needed. Add the drained pasta and remaining parsley to the sauce, then stir to combine. Divide among plates and top with a sprinkle of @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g} and a spoonful of salsa. Enjoy!

> Our Veggie Bolognese is a delicious veggie option that makes it easy to eat more veg in your diet and try something new!